00:01:35.62 --> 00:01:40.18
This is the CBS Evening News with Norah O'Donnell reporting

00:01:40.18 --> 00:01:41.93
from the nation's capital.

00:01:41.93 --> 00:01:43.60
Good evening to our viewers in the West.

00:01:43.60 --> 00:01:45.11
And thank you for joining us.

00:01:45.11 --> 00:01:47.59
We want to begin with what is the biggest security

00:01:47.59 --> 00:01:49.36
crisis between the West and Russia

00:01:49.36 --> 00:01:51.52
since the end of the Cold War.

00:01:51.52 --> 00:01:53.59
In his first address, specifically

00:01:53.59 --> 00:01:55.36
about the tensions, President Biden today

00:01:55.36 --> 00:01:59.38
revealed a new number of Russian troops now encircling Ukraine--

00:01:59.38 --> 00:02:02.29
150,000 soldiers.

00:02:02.29 --> 00:02:05.95
The president says the US stands prepared to respond,

00:02:05.95 --> 00:02:08.77
and that an invasion by Putin would rally the world

00:02:08.77 --> 00:02:10.63
to oppose its aggression.

00:02:10.63 --> 00:02:13.30
A US official tells CBN News that Russia

00:02:13.30 --> 00:02:16.18
moved rocket launchers and long-range artillery

00:02:16.18 --> 00:02:18.88
into firing positions yesterday.

00:02:18.88 --> 00:02:21.79
Earlier today, the websites of Ukraine's defense ministry,

00:02:21.79 --> 00:02:24.43
armed forces, and two state-owned banks

00:02:24.43 --> 00:02:26.98
were brought down by a cyber attack.

00:02:26.98 --> 00:02:29.86
Ukraine's government released a statement suggesting Russians

00:02:29.86 --> 00:02:31.03
were the perpetrators.

00:02:31.03 --> 00:02:33.79
And experts have long said electronic warfare could

00:02:33.79 --> 00:02:35.66
be a precursor to invasion.

00:02:35.66 --> 00:02:38.35
CBS's Charlie D'Agata is on the ground in Ukraine.

00:02:38.35 --> 00:02:40.27
But we're going to start with CBS's Ed O'Keefe

00:02:40.27 --> 00:02:41.06
at the White House.

00:02:41.06 --> 00:02:42.53
Good evening, Ed.

00:02:42.53 --> 00:02:43.36
Good evening, Norah.

00:02:43.36 --> 00:02:45.64
There is deep skepticism here at the White House

00:02:45.64 --> 00:02:47.77
about that purported Russian troop pullback.

00:02:47.77 --> 00:02:51.07
The president warns an invasion of Ukraine is still possible.

00:02:51.07 --> 00:02:53.38
But he had a message today for the Russian leader.

00:02:53.38 --> 00:02:56.26
Give peace a chance.

00:02:56.26 --> 00:02:58.69
President Biden said today he isn't convinced

00:02:58.69 --> 00:03:00.76
Vladimir Putin is pulling back Russian troops

00:03:00.76 --> 00:03:02.26
from the Ukrainian border.

00:03:02.26 --> 00:03:06.49
That would be good, but we have not yet verified that.

00:03:06.49 --> 00:03:10.54
Indeed, our analysts indicate that they remain very much

00:03:10.54 --> 00:03:12.28
in a threatening position.

00:03:12.28 --> 00:03:14.17
Russian state media today showed what

00:03:14.17 --> 00:03:16.54
appeared to be some Russian tanks retreating.

00:03:16.54 --> 00:03:19.57
Putin announced he had decided to partially pull back troops.

00:03:19.57 --> 00:03:21.85
But a US official called the apparent withdrawal

00:03:21.85 --> 00:03:23.00
a smokescreen.

00:03:23.00 --> 00:03:26.08
And the president revealed there are now 150,000 Russian troops

00:03:26.08 --> 00:03:29.26
encircling Ukraine, up from 130,000.

00:03:29.26 --> 00:03:32.63
An invasion remains distinctly possible.

00:03:32.63 --> 00:03:34.03
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:03:34.03 --> 00:03:35.56
The president's comments came hours

00:03:35.56 --> 00:03:38.47
after Putin, meeting in Moscow with the German chancellor,

00:03:38.47 --> 00:03:40.39
said he didn't want war, and that he

00:03:40.39 --> 00:03:43.54
wanted to solve the issue as part of a negotiation process

00:03:43.54 --> 00:03:45.01
through peaceful means.

00:03:45.01 --> 00:03:48.43
We should give the diplomacy every chance to succeed.

00:03:48.43 --> 00:03:51.47
President Biden said diplomacy was still the preferred option.

00:03:51.47 --> 00:03:53.20
But he made clear that Putin's demand

00:03:53.20 --> 00:03:55.51
that Ukraine never become a member of NATO

00:03:55.51 --> 00:03:57.05
is off the table.

00:03:57.05 --> 00:03:59.20
He also had a warning for Putin.

00:03:59.20 --> 00:04:01.39
Though I've been clear that if Russia

00:04:01.39 --> 00:04:06.07
targets Americans in Ukraine, we will respond forcefully.

00:04:06.07 --> 00:04:08.65
Mr. Biden's speech today is his first on the crisis

00:04:08.65 --> 00:04:10.75
amid weeks of diplomatic talks, including

00:04:10.75 --> 00:04:12.58
a call today with the French president

00:04:12.58 --> 00:04:15.19
and the deployment of thousands of US troops to NATO

00:04:15.19 --> 00:04:16.66
countries in Eastern Europe.

00:04:16.66 --> 00:04:20.08
Members of the 82nd Airborne left for Poland today.

00:04:20.08 --> 00:04:23.56
But the president made a point of explicitly stating the US

00:04:23.56 --> 00:04:26.62
and NATO a threat to Russia.

00:04:26.62 --> 00:04:29.12
We're not targeting the people of Russia.

00:04:29.12 --> 00:04:32.44
We do not seek to destabilize Russia.

00:04:32.44 --> 00:04:37.55
To the citizens of Russia, you are not our enemy.

00:04:37.55 --> 00:04:39.83
Now despite Putin's claims that he's pulling back

00:04:39.83 --> 00:04:42.23
troops in the hopes for broader diplomatic talks,

00:04:42.23 --> 00:04:45.95
US officials tell CBS News an invasion of Ukraine by Russia

00:04:45.95 --> 00:04:48.53
could still occur later this week.

00:04:48.53 --> 00:04:49.25
Norah.

00:04:49.25 --> 00:04:51.56
Ed O'Keefe at the White House, thanks.

00:04:51.56 --> 00:04:54.59
The secretary of defense will head to Poland this week

00:04:54.59 --> 00:04:56.63
to meet US troops in the NATO country.

00:04:56.63 --> 00:05:00.65
And that's where the US has deployed 5,000 service members

00:05:00.65 --> 00:05:03.80
in hopes of hardening the alliance's eastern flank.

00:05:03.80 --> 00:05:07.55
It's out of concern that Russia could steamroll through Ukraine

00:05:07.55 --> 00:05:10.91
and move to take the former Soviet Republic of Moldova.

00:05:10.91 --> 00:05:14.45
That would put Vladimir Putin on the doorstep of NATO.

00:05:14.45 --> 00:05:17.09
And as President Biden said today, attacking one NATO

00:05:17.09 --> 00:05:19.04
country is attacking them all.

00:05:19.04 --> 00:05:22.04
CBS's Charlie D'Agata is in Lviv, Ukraine,

00:05:22.04 --> 00:05:25.01
near Poland's border and the new temporary home of the US

00:05:25.01 --> 00:05:25.64
embassy.

00:05:25.64 --> 00:05:28.51
Good evening, Charlie.

00:05:28.51 --> 00:05:30.16
Norah, the president's address came

00:05:30.16 --> 00:05:33.04
a bit late for any official reaction here.

00:05:33.04 --> 00:05:36.43
Ukrainians will be hopeful the US is open to negotiations

00:05:36.43 --> 00:05:42.10
but realistically more fearful of what may come.

00:05:42.10 --> 00:05:44.59
The Russian threat still has Ukraine

00:05:44.59 --> 00:05:47.77
skeptical and on edge tonight.

00:05:47.77 --> 00:05:51.01
The foreign minister saying we believe in a de-escalation

00:05:51.01 --> 00:05:54.88
when we see a full scale pullout.

00:05:54.88 --> 00:05:58.06
Despite Russian reassurances, US officials

00:05:58.06 --> 00:06:01.48
tell CBS News those troops pulling back to their barracks

00:06:01.48 --> 00:06:05.80
are not frontline forces, describing them as irrelevant.

00:06:05.80 --> 00:06:07.66
And they represent just a fraction

00:06:07.66 --> 00:06:11.14
of the rest of the 150,000 troops,

00:06:11.14 --> 00:06:13.69
missiles, and warships that remain

00:06:13.69 --> 00:06:16.63
in place by land and sea.

00:06:16.63 --> 00:06:19.12
Critically, that includes Russian troops

00:06:19.12 --> 00:06:22.63
on joint military exercises in Belarus

00:06:22.63 --> 00:06:25.90
just a few miles from the capital Kiev.

00:06:25.90 --> 00:06:29.35
A US official tells CBS News that Russian forces have

00:06:29.35 --> 00:06:31.54
moved into attack positions.

00:06:31.54 --> 00:06:35.02
And Americans have been told to leave immediately.

00:06:35.02 --> 00:06:38.47
It's unclear how many of the thousands of US citizens

00:06:38.47 --> 00:06:41.47
living in Ukraine still remain here.

00:06:41.47 --> 00:06:45.10
Some like Keith Morrison have sought safer refuge

00:06:45.10 --> 00:06:49.72
here in Lviv but no plans to cross the Polish border.

00:06:49.72 --> 00:06:51.22
A full-scale invasion?

00:06:51.22 --> 00:06:52.57
I mean, yeah, sure.

00:06:52.57 --> 00:06:54.82
If troops are coming to Lviv, that would definitely

00:06:54.82 --> 00:06:57.07
influence our decision.

00:06:57.07 --> 00:07:00.16
Now there was that major cyber attack

00:07:00.16 --> 00:07:02.38
that you mentioned earlier tonight.

00:07:02.38 --> 00:07:04.84
It shut down the websites of the ministry of defense

00:07:04.84 --> 00:07:06.41
and a couple of major banks.

00:07:06.41 --> 00:07:08.71
Everything was up and running in a couple of hours.

00:07:08.71 --> 00:07:10.81
People that we spoke to said it was probably

00:07:10.81 --> 00:07:13.03
something to test the system.

00:07:13.03 --> 00:07:14.23
Norah.

00:07:14.23 --> 00:07:16.73
Charlie D'Agata in Lviv, thank you.

00:07:16.73 --> 00:07:18.46
Well, tonight, President Biden warns

00:07:18.46 --> 00:07:22.06
that harsh sanctions on Russia could have significant blowback

00:07:22.06 --> 00:07:24.88
on the US economy, including possible price

00:07:24.88 --> 00:07:27.76
hikes and disruption to the nation's energy supply.

00:07:27.76 --> 00:07:31.58
A gallon of gas is now about $1 more than it was a year ago.

00:07:31.58 --> 00:07:36.34
And we get more from CBS's Omar Villafranca.

00:07:36.34 --> 00:07:39.79
Filling up your gas tank can empty your wallet.

00:07:39.79 --> 00:07:42.07
California has some of the highest prices,

00:07:42.07 --> 00:07:44.50
an average of $4.71 a gallon.

00:07:44.50 --> 00:07:48.91
This station near downtown LA was well over $6.

00:07:48.91 --> 00:07:50.59
Holy mackerel.

00:07:50.59 --> 00:07:51.68
I couldn't believe it.

00:07:51.68 --> 00:07:52.48
It was crazy.

00:07:52.48 --> 00:07:55.15
Texas has some of the cheapest prices in the country,

00:07:55.15 --> 00:07:57.16
an average of $3.18 a gallon.

00:07:57.16 --> 00:07:59.80
But that's no relief to Eduardo Martinez,

00:07:59.80 --> 00:08:02.59
who drives more than 100 miles a day

00:08:02.59 --> 00:08:04.24
hauling construction debris.

00:08:04.24 --> 00:08:06.76
How often are you having to fill up?

00:08:06.76 --> 00:08:09.14
Maybe like once-- once or twice a day.

00:08:09.14 --> 00:08:09.64
Yeah.

00:08:09.64 --> 00:08:11.93
How much is it to fill your tank up?

00:08:11.93 --> 00:08:13.24
Well over $100.

00:08:13.24 --> 00:08:15.91
It looks like we're in for higher oil and gasoline

00:08:15.91 --> 00:08:18.13
prices for the long haul.

00:08:18.13 --> 00:08:21.25
Ed Hirs is an energy fellow at the University of Houston

00:08:21.25 --> 00:08:24.88
and says despite the president releasing 50 million barrels

00:08:24.88 --> 00:08:27.67
of oil from the Strategic Reserve to help consumers,

00:08:27.67 --> 00:08:30.88
it's just a drop in the bucket on the global market.

00:08:30.88 --> 00:08:34.60
Hirs says if oil-rich Russia invades Ukraine,

00:08:34.60 --> 00:08:38.47
American consumers will feel the ripple effect at the pump.

00:08:38.47 --> 00:08:45.04
Expect to see the price go up by another $0.50 to $0.75 a gallon

00:08:45.04 --> 00:08:50.31
if Russia goes ahead with an invasion of Ukraine.

00:08:50.31 --> 00:08:52.73
President Biden says he will work with Congress to protect

00:08:52.73 --> 00:08:54.38
consumers at the pump.

00:08:54.38 --> 00:08:57.44
Senate Democrats are considering a federal gas tax holiday

00:08:57.44 --> 00:08:59.21
which would last the rest of the year

00:08:59.21 --> 00:09:02.33
and could save consumers up to $0.18 a gallon.

00:09:02.33 --> 00:09:05.45
But it's too early to tell if the bill has enough support.

00:09:05.45 --> 00:09:06.47
Norah.

00:09:06.47 --> 00:09:08.81
Omar Villafranca, thanks.

00:09:08.81 --> 00:09:10.67
Tonight, in an historic settlement,

00:09:10.67 --> 00:09:12.50
a gun manufacturer for the first time

00:09:12.50 --> 00:09:14.93
is being held liable for a mass shooting.

00:09:14.93 --> 00:09:18.95
Nearly 10 years after 20 first graders and six educators

00:09:18.95 --> 00:09:21.05
were killed at Sandy Hook Elementary.

00:09:21.05 --> 00:09:24.50
The families of nine victims have reached a $73 million

00:09:24.50 --> 00:09:27.41
settlement with Remington, the maker of the rifle used

00:09:27.41 --> 00:09:28.47
in the attack.

00:09:28.47 --> 00:09:32.33
We get more now from CBS's Nikki Battiste.

00:09:32.33 --> 00:09:34.97
I'm very hopeful that this creates precedent.

00:09:34.97 --> 00:09:37.25
After the murder of her six-year-old son

00:09:37.25 --> 00:09:39.59
Dylan at Sandy Hook Elementary School,

00:09:39.59 --> 00:09:41.99
Nikole Hockley fought for change.

00:09:41.99 --> 00:09:44.09
She's among nine victims' families

00:09:44.09 --> 00:09:46.61
who took on Remington, manufacturers

00:09:46.61 --> 00:09:49.22
of the semi-automatic AR-15 style

00:09:49.22 --> 00:09:51.41
rifle used in the massacre.

00:09:51.41 --> 00:09:53.33
They will tell you this is made for hunting.

00:09:53.33 --> 00:09:55.39
But where's the animal?

00:09:55.39 --> 00:09:56.77
Where's the animal in this?

00:09:56.77 --> 00:09:58.51
Attorneys representing the families

00:09:58.51 --> 00:10:01.72
were able to navigate around a federal law designed

00:10:01.72 --> 00:10:04.24
to protect gun companies from litigation,

00:10:04.24 --> 00:10:07.66
arguing that Remington chose profit over safety

00:10:07.66 --> 00:10:12.16
and deliberately marketed the AR-15 to troubled young men.

00:10:12.16 --> 00:10:13.81
I know that the headlines today are

00:10:13.81 --> 00:10:18.75
going to be a lot about the $73 million.

00:10:18.75 --> 00:10:22.99
That is just not really on my radar.

00:10:22.99 --> 00:10:24.91
It's more about the process of what we can now

00:10:24.91 --> 00:10:27.28
do with what we've discovered and how we can share that

00:10:27.28 --> 00:10:28.48
to everyone else.

00:10:28.48 --> 00:10:31.75
Back in December 2012, the 20-year-old gunman

00:10:31.75 --> 00:10:34.54
entered the school and began a shooting rampage,

00:10:34.54 --> 00:10:37.42
killing 20 first graders and six teachers

00:10:37.42 --> 00:10:39.58
before taking his own life.

00:10:39.58 --> 00:10:41.89
Vicki was an incredible person.

00:10:41.89 --> 00:10:44.08
Jillian and Matthew Soto are siblings

00:10:44.08 --> 00:10:48.07
of 27-year-old Victoria Soto, a teacher who died

00:10:48.07 --> 00:10:50.14
trying to protect her students.

00:10:50.14 --> 00:10:51.64
Why was it important for your family

00:10:51.64 --> 00:10:54.07
to be a part of this lawsuit against Remington?

00:10:54.07 --> 00:10:56.74
We are sending a message to gun companies

00:10:56.74 --> 00:11:00.62
and to insurance companies that your products are dangerous.

00:11:00.62 --> 00:11:03.94
And you can be held liable for the deaths that

00:11:03.94 --> 00:11:05.44
come from these products.

00:11:05.44 --> 00:11:08.29
It gives us hope that people are going

00:11:08.29 --> 00:11:12.82
to remember who died at Sandy Hook, who Vicki is,

00:11:12.82 --> 00:11:16.33
and the fight that these families have put up

00:11:16.33 --> 00:11:19.87
to see this not happen again.

00:11:19.87 --> 00:11:22.96
Remington, which has now filed for bankruptcy twice,

00:11:22.96 --> 00:11:26.08
has not responded to CBS News request for comment.

00:11:26.08 --> 00:11:28.45
Lawyers for the nine Sandy Hook families

00:11:28.45 --> 00:11:30.43
say the gunmaker did agree to make

00:11:30.43 --> 00:11:33.52
all of its marketing materials public as a part

00:11:33.52 --> 00:11:34.39
of the settlement.

00:11:34.39 --> 00:11:34.89
Norah.

00:11:34.89 --> 00:11:38.29
Nikki Battiste, thank you.

00:11:38.29 --> 00:11:40.99
Now to a major development in the sex abuse scandal

