00:12:11.52 --> 00:12:14.55
and as a result of unfair public attacks."

00:12:14.55 --> 00:12:16.77
How much pressure was Prince Andrew

00:12:16.77 --> 00:12:19.74
under by the royal family to settle?

00:12:19.74 --> 00:12:21.63
Everyone in the royal family was obviously

00:12:21.63 --> 00:12:25.14
very keen to avert a full-blown trial.

00:12:25.14 --> 00:12:28.17
The settlement comes just weeks before the Queen's second son

00:12:28.17 --> 00:12:30.48
was set to be deposed under oath.

00:12:30.48 --> 00:12:35.34
There is no doubt in my mind that the possibility of his

00:12:35.34 --> 00:12:40.38
being dismantled piece by piece, question by question,

00:12:40.38 --> 00:12:43.65
and his character being shattered

00:12:43.65 --> 00:12:47.04
to pieces during the course of a deposition, those

00:12:47.04 --> 00:12:49.95
are the reasons that Prince Andrew would settle

00:12:49.95 --> 00:12:52.56
At the heart of the case is Giuffre's accusation

00:12:52.56 --> 00:12:55.38
that convicted sex offender, the late Jeffrey Epstein,

00:12:55.38 --> 00:12:58.14
trafficked her to the prince in the early 2000s

00:12:58.14 --> 00:13:02.10
when she was just a teenager and says she was raped by Andrew,

00:13:02.10 --> 00:13:04.53
a charge the prince denies.

00:13:04.53 --> 00:13:08.10
I have no recollection of ever meeting this lady.

00:13:08.10 --> 00:13:11.67
Is Prince Andrew's settlement an admission of guilt?

00:13:11.67 --> 00:13:15.51
Prince Andrew's settlement is clearly not an admission

00:13:15.51 --> 00:13:17.13
of guilt on his part.

00:13:17.13 --> 00:13:20.52
And it was drafted specifically that way.

00:13:20.52 --> 00:13:23.55
Andrew acknowledged Epstein's trafficking of young girls

00:13:23.55 --> 00:13:26.76
and says he now regrets his association with him,

00:13:26.76 --> 00:13:29.85
adding that he'll also be making a donation to Giuffre's

00:13:29.85 --> 00:13:31.43
charity.

00:13:31.43 --> 00:13:33.72
Norah, Buckingham Palace has declined to comment.

00:13:33.72 --> 00:13:36.21
But the deal avoids further potential embarrassment

00:13:36.21 --> 00:13:38.73
for the royal family as the Queen celebrates

00:13:38.73 --> 00:13:41.76
70 years on the throne.

00:13:41.76 --> 00:13:43.74
Ian Lee in London, thanks.

00:13:43.74 --> 00:13:47.43
Well, a jury today ruled against former Alaska governor Sarah

00:13:47.43 --> 00:13:50.43
Palin in her libel suit with The New York Times.

00:13:50.43 --> 00:13:53.67
The jurors in a federal court rejected her claim

00:13:53.67 --> 00:13:56.58
that the paper maliciously damaged her reputation

00:13:56.58 --> 00:14:00.04
by falsely linking her campaign rhetoric to a mass shooting.

00:14:00.04 --> 00:14:02.16
A judge had already declared that if the jury sided

00:14:02.16 --> 00:14:05.01
with Palin, he would set aside its verdict on the grounds

00:14:05.01 --> 00:14:08.88
that she hadn't proved that the paper acted maliciously.

00:14:08.88 --> 00:14:11.31
Let's turn now to the Olympics where the Russian doping

00:14:11.31 --> 00:14:14.13
scandal remains the biggest topic of conversation.

00:14:14.13 --> 00:14:17.85
Russia's 15-year-old skating sensation returned to the ice

00:14:17.85 --> 00:14:20.10
today with a powerful performance.

00:14:20.10 --> 00:14:22.14
But it did little to quiet the criticism

00:14:22.14 --> 00:14:24.03
over her failed drug test.

00:14:24.03 --> 00:14:28.28
CBS's Jamie Yuccas is in Beijing with the latest.

00:14:28.28 --> 00:14:33.05
After days of drama off the ice, Russian star Kamila Valieva

00:14:33.05 --> 00:14:35.63
returned to the competition, stumbling

00:14:35.63 --> 00:14:37.91
while attempting her first triple Axel

00:14:37.91 --> 00:14:41.18
but quickly recovered skating into the lead heading

00:14:41.18 --> 00:14:44.21
into the finals of the women's individual program.

00:14:44.21 --> 00:14:47.15
Valieva has been under a cloud of suspicion

00:14:47.15 --> 00:14:49.64
after failing a drug test in December.

00:14:49.64 --> 00:14:51.86
She was cleared to compete in the Olympics.

00:14:51.86 --> 00:14:54.56
But the IOC said there will be no medal

00:14:54.56 --> 00:14:57.20
ceremony until the doping charges against her

00:14:57.20 --> 00:14:58.21
are resolved.

00:14:58.21 --> 00:15:00.08
I thought she handled it with a lot of grace.

00:15:00.08 --> 00:15:02.21
Stephanie Apstein of Sports Illustrated

00:15:02.21 --> 00:15:04.73
watched Valieva from inside the arena.

00:15:04.73 --> 00:15:08.12
I was watching it behind the heads of the skaters who

00:15:08.12 --> 00:15:10.46
were saying that they believe in clean sports,

00:15:10.46 --> 00:15:11.78
and that doping is wrong.

00:15:11.78 --> 00:15:14.03
And I think it was another reminder for me

00:15:14.03 --> 00:15:18.21
of how this isn't really about the skating at all anymore.

00:15:18.21 --> 00:15:20.42
It's about whether she should be there.

00:15:20.42 --> 00:15:22.82
Olympic officials said today Valieva

00:15:22.82 --> 00:15:25.07
blamed her positive test on a mix up

00:15:25.07 --> 00:15:27.41
with her grandfather's heart medication.

00:15:27.41 --> 00:15:30.32
Results on a second sample are pending.

00:15:30.32 --> 00:15:33.32
In her first public comments since the scandal broke,

00:15:33.32 --> 00:15:35.93
Valieva told a Russian state broadcaster,

00:15:35.93 --> 00:15:38.36
"these days have been very difficult for me.

00:15:38.36 --> 00:15:41.96
I'm happy but I'm tired emotionally."

00:15:41.96 --> 00:15:44.81
Tonight, The New York Times is reporting that Valieva's tests

00:15:44.81 --> 00:15:47.60
found evidence of two other heart medications

00:15:47.60 --> 00:15:49.16
not on the banned list.

00:15:49.16 --> 00:15:52.76
One anti-doping official though said the presence of all three

00:15:52.76 --> 00:15:55.85
of those drugs in an athlete the age of Valieva

00:15:55.85 --> 00:15:57.77
is highly unusual.

00:15:57.77 --> 00:15:58.70
Norah.

00:15:58.70 --> 00:15:59.57
And puzzling.

00:15:59.57 --> 00:16:02.06
Jamie Yuccas in Beijing, thanks.

00:16:02.06 --> 00:16:04.64
Well, a frightening moment aboard an American Airlines

00:16:04.64 --> 00:16:06.62
flight right before takeoff today.

00:16:06.62 --> 00:16:09.65
The plane was on the tarmac at New York's JFK airport

00:16:09.65 --> 00:16:12.95
heading to Phoenix when two tires blew out.

00:16:12.95 --> 00:16:15.71
And the pilot had to suddenly abort takeoff.

00:16:15.71 --> 00:16:16.73
No one was hurt.

00:16:16.73 --> 00:16:20.36
All 142 passengers on board had to reschedule

00:16:20.36 --> 00:16:22.13
for a later flight.

00:16:22.13 --> 00:16:25.52
And still ahead right here on tonight's CBS Evening News,

00:16:25.52 --> 00:16:27.32
Alec Baldwin is hit with a lawsuit

00:16:27.32 --> 00:16:29.24
over that deadly accidental shooting

00:16:29.24 --> 00:16:30.95
on the set of his movie.

00:16:30.95 --> 00:16:36.48


00:16:36.48 --> 00:16:38.82
Police in upstate New York have found a young girl

00:16:38.82 --> 00:16:40.74
reported missing in 2019.

00:16:40.74 --> 00:16:43.80
The six-year-old was discovered in a secret room hidden

00:16:43.80 --> 00:16:47.01
under a staircase in the home where her biological parents

00:16:47.01 --> 00:16:47.67
were living.

00:16:47.67 --> 00:16:49.66
Police credit an eagle-eyed detective

00:16:49.66 --> 00:16:52.20
who noticed an odd section of the staircase that appeared out

00:16:52.20 --> 00:16:55.11
of place, and they spotted a blanket.

00:16:55.11 --> 00:16:57.00
Actor Alec Baldwin was sued today

00:16:57.00 --> 00:16:59.58
by the family of the cinematographer he accidentally

00:16:59.58 --> 00:17:02.61
shot and killed on the set of his western Rust.

00:17:02.61 --> 00:17:04.71
A lawyer for the family of Halyna Hutchins

00:17:04.71 --> 00:17:07.14
blames her death on, quote, "reckless conduct

00:17:07.14 --> 00:17:10.62
and cost-cutting measures by Baldwin and other producers."

00:17:10.62 --> 00:17:13.86
Baldwin claims he never pulled the trigger.

00:17:13.86 --> 00:17:16.38
Well, there's big news tonight from our parent company.

00:17:16.38 --> 00:17:20.19
ViacomCBS will be known as Paramount starting Wednesday.

00:17:20.19 --> 00:17:22.71
CBS, one of the founding names in broadcasting

00:17:22.71 --> 00:17:24.94
for nearly a century, will remain the same.

00:17:24.94 --> 00:17:26.94
The company announced the rebranding today

00:17:26.94 --> 00:17:29.67
while also revealing that its streaming platform Paramount

00:17:29.67 --> 00:17:33.30
Plus and Showtime topped 56 million subscribers

00:17:33.30 --> 00:17:35.43
at the end of 2021.

00:17:35.43 --> 00:17:38.13
And coming up next, meet the orchestra

00:17:38.13 --> 00:17:42.24
hoping to erase the stigma of mental illness one note

00:17:42.24 --> 00:17:44.83
at a time.

00:17:44.83 --> 00:17:48.05
If you can't watch the CBS Evening News, you can listen.

00:17:48.05 --> 00:17:50.18
Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts.

00:17:50.18 --> 00:17:52.06
Sponsored by Principal Financial Group.

00:17:52.06 --> 00:17:56.81


00:17:56.81 --> 00:17:58.24
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:58.24 --> 00:18:00.85
Studies have long found that listening to music

00:18:00.85 --> 00:18:02.56
benefits our mental health.

00:18:02.56 --> 00:18:04.84
CBS's Nancy Chen highlights an orchestra

00:18:04.84 --> 00:18:08.90
where the musicians themselves are the ones benefiting.

00:18:08.90 --> 00:18:11.56
[ORCHESTRA MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:11.56 --> 00:18:14.11
There have been plenty of high and low notes

00:18:14.11 --> 00:18:18.40
for those on stage here at Boston's storied Symphony Hall.

00:18:18.40 --> 00:18:20.65
But when these musicians perform together,

00:18:20.65 --> 00:18:23.00
there is simply harmony.

00:18:23.00 --> 00:18:25.16
What does music bring to your life?

00:18:25.16 --> 00:18:28.22
Music brings to my life everything.

00:18:28.22 --> 00:18:31.22
Ronald Brownstein was once a music director at Julliard

00:18:31.22 --> 00:18:33.90
and conducted around the world.

00:18:33.90 --> 00:18:39.95
I was able to learn and memorize complete symphonies overnight.

00:18:39.95 --> 00:18:41.63
But then the award-winning conductor

00:18:41.63 --> 00:18:43.67
was diagnosed with bipolar disorder,

00:18:43.67 --> 00:18:45.17
which he says cost him work.

00:18:45.17 --> 00:18:47.03
It was a constant up and down.

00:18:47.03 --> 00:18:50.21
I just want an orchestra of people like me.

00:18:50.21 --> 00:18:53.93
Along with his wife, Brownstein started the Me2/Orchestra

00:18:53.93 --> 00:18:57.71
for people with mental illness and those who support them,

00:18:57.71 --> 00:19:00.08
musicians like Josh Santana.

00:19:00.08 --> 00:19:02.75
What have you found with the orchestra?

00:19:02.75 --> 00:19:07.58
Playing music is so powerful when you are all

00:19:07.58 --> 00:19:09.20
joined by a common mission.

00:19:09.20 --> 00:19:12.32
The New England-based orchestra has inspired ensembles around

00:19:12.32 --> 00:19:14.96
the country, all with the same focus--

00:19:14.96 --> 00:19:16.70
ending the stigma.

00:19:16.70 --> 00:19:18.64
We aren't trying to be the greatest

00:19:18.64 --> 00:19:20.14
orchestra in the world.

00:19:20.14 --> 00:19:21.90
We are just trying to create a community.

00:19:21.90 --> 00:19:24.43
[ORCHESTRA MUSIC PLAYING]

00:19:24.43 --> 00:19:30.20
A community orchestrating inclusion and appreciation.

00:19:30.20 --> 00:19:34.54
Nancy Chen, CBS News.

00:19:34.54 --> 00:19:35.14
Perfect.

00:19:35.14 --> 00:19:37.46
We'll be right back.

00:19:37.46 --> 00:19:41.37
This portion of the CBS Evening News is sponsored by Farxiga.

00:19:41.37 --> 00:19:46.51


